In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation to celebrate Labor Day and honor the American worker. The proclamation highlights the administration's efforts to prioritize the well-being and economic interests of American workers, including tax cuts, deregulation, energy development, and trade reforms. The administration has also taken steps to uphold immigration laws and protect job opportunities for American workers. President Trump emphasizes the importance of investing in education and job training to ensure good-paying jobs for all Americans. The proclamation also acknowledges the role of labor unions in advocating for workers' interests and promises fair trade agreements that benefit American workers. Overall, the proclamation aims to recognize and honor the contributions and resilience of working Americans.